    <text>
        <body>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="event" xml:id="factoid-1" resp="#dschwartz">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/3051-1</idno>
                <listEvent>
                    <event ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/letters http://syriaca.org/keyword/baptism http://syriaca.org/keyword/anointing http://syriaca.org/keyword/chalcedonians" notBefore="0513" notAfter="0518">
                        <desc>
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/51">Severus</persName> wrote a letter to the
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/3060">monastery at Tagai</placeName> 
                            stating that re-baptism and re-anointing are not required
                            of those who repent of their Chalcedonianism.
                        </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/669"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">283-86</citedRange>
                    <citedRange unit="part">V.3</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="relation" xml:id="factoid-2" resp="#dschwartz">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/3051-2</idno>
                <listRelation>
                    <relation type="person" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/professional-relationship" mutual="http://syriaca.org/person/51 http://syriaca.org/person/2724">
                        <desc>
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/51">Severus</persName> and <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2724">Neon</persName> 
                            had a professional relationship.
                        </desc>
                    </relation>
                </listRelation>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/669"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">283</citedRange>
                    <citedRange unit="part">V.3</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="occupation" xml:id="factoid-3" resp="#dschwartz">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/3051-3</idno>
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2724"/>
                        <occupation ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/priests">
                            <note type="desc">
                                <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2724">Neon</persName> 
                                was a presbyter.
                            </note>
                        </occupation>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/669"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">283</citedRange>
                    <citedRange unit="part">V.3</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="occupation" xml:id="factoid-4" resp="#dschwartz">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/3051-4</idno>
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2724"/>
                        <occupation ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/monastic-heads">
                            <note type="desc">
                                <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2724">Neon</persName> 
                                was an archimandrites.
                            </note>
                        </occupation>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/669"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">283</citedRange>
                    <citedRange unit="part">V.3</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="event" xml:id="factoid-5" resp="#dschwartz">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/3051-5</idno>
                <listEvent>
                    <event ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/heresy http://syriaca.org/keyword/chalcedonians http://syriaca.org/keyword/baptism http://syriaca.org/keyword/anointing" when="0513">
                        <desc>
                            When <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/51">Severus</persName> became bishop of 
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2610">Antioch</placeName>, he opposed those who
                            insisted that Chalcedonians who repented of their theology needed to be
                            re-baptized or re-annointed.
                        </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/669"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">284</citedRange>
                    <citedRange unit="part">V.3</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="event" xml:id="factoid-6" resp="#dschwartz">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/3051-6</idno>
                <listEvent>
                    <event ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/heresy http://syriaca.org/keyword/chalcedonians http://syriaca.org/keyword/baptism http://syriaca.org/keyword/anointing">
                        <desc>
                            When <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2759">Stephen</persName>
                            united with bishops in the regions of
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/698">Palestine</placeName> and 
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2734">Alexandria</placeName> he opposed those who
                            insisted that Chalcedonians who repented of their theology needed to be
                            re-baptized or re-annointed.
                        </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/669"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">284</citedRange>
                    <citedRange unit="part">V.3</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
